%N A396143 Triangle T(n,k), n >= 0, 0 <= k <= n, read by rows, where T(n,k) is the number of strict integer partitions of 2*n with reverse-alternating sum -2*k.
%C A396143 Also the number of partitions of n+2*k^2 into 2*k distinct parts not containing the part 2*k, except when n = k = 0.
%H A396143 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A396143/b396143.txt">Rows n = 0..139, flattened</a>
%F A396143 G.f. of column k: Sum_{i=1..2*k} q^(i^2+k) * q_binomial(2*k-1,i-1) / Product_{j=1..i} (1-q^j) for k > 0.
%F A396143 T(n,k) + A344649(n,k) = A152146(n,k), except when n = k = 0.
%e A396143 Triangle begins:
